The paper deals with the construction and analysis of deterministic sensing matrices for compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of the LASSO algorithm for signal recovery suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The mention of experimental results and measurement of accuracy and complexity suggests a focus on numerical analysis (cs.NA) and possibly optimization (cs.MM).
